'When we wait, our guard is down. Soldiers relax and forget they are in a great war. I fear that our eyes do not watch Adambel as well as they could, or as well as they should! Would you put me at ease and patrol the wall of Adambel? It should not take very long, and I would feel much better!'
Habhûk can be found at Adambel.\n\nYou should talk to Habhûk.
'When we wait, our guard is down.'
'Nothing to report? I am relieved, friend.'
'Nothing to report? I am relieved, my helpful friend! Oh, my mind does wander when I have nothing to do. I am glad that Adambel is safe. Let us keep it that way!'
Habhûk is worried that Adambel may not be properly patrolled.
